CUDA Batch Signal Smoother - Install and Run
============================================

Prerequisites
-------------
1. Linux environment
2. NVIDIA GPU with CUDA support
3. CUDA Toolkit (nvcc available in PATH)
4. Python 3.8+ (standard library only — no pip installs needed)
5. make

Build and Run
-------------
From the repository root:

    chmod +x run.sh
    ./run.sh

Manual Commands (optional)
--------------------------
1. Generate input dataset:
   python3 src/generate_dataset.py \
       --output data/input --count 200 --length 1024 --noise 0.25

2. Build executable:
   make

3. Run smoother:
   ./bin/batch_signal_smoother data/input data/output

Optional flags for generate_dataset.py
---------------------------------------
  --count   N      Number of signals (default 200)
  --length  N      Samples per signal (default 1024)
  --noise   F      White-noise std-dev (default 0.25)
  --seed    N      Base random seed    (default 42)

Output Artifacts
----------------
1. Smoothed signal files (float32 binary):
   data/output/smoothed_0000.bin … smoothed_0199.bin

2. Execution proof log:
   data/output/run_log.txt
   (contains timestamp, signal dimensions, kernel time, throughput)

Cleaning Up
-----------
    make clean      # removes binary and all generated data files
